					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of 17th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>372 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>195</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>150</height>
										<width>110</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>372 folios (+ 1 modern paper flyleaf at the beginning and 2 at the end).</p>
									<p>Hebrew foliation preserved almost throughout.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 9 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Imperfect at the beginning.</p>
									<p>Folios missing after folio 304.</p>
									<p>Slightly water-damaged. </p>
									<p>Last leaves slightly worm-eaten.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="21" writtenLines="21">
									<p>Catchwords (vertical, inclined) on every verso.</p>
									<p>Initial words given in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Running title on every recto.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Oriental semi-cursive scripts of 17th century.The main scribe inscribed in the colophon as <name type="person" role="scribe">Yosef Motsri</name>, folio 368v. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="369r" to="372v"/>due to a different hand.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>The last six leaves belonged to a different manuscript. Contain midrashic expositions on parashah Ṿa-yelekh and Ha᾿azinu. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Mikha᾿el ben Mosheh</name>: inscribed, folio 2r. </p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Raḥamim ben Shemu᾿el Malki</name>owner: inscribed, folio 369r. </p>
						</additions>
